overview: >-
  The user wanted to significantly improve the aesthetics of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which they felt was too generic. The agent began by
  thoroughly analyzing the existing visual design, identifying areas like the
  color palette, typography, spacing, form elements, and overall visual interest
  as needing improvement.

  The approach involved implementing a new, calming sleep-themed color palette,
  redesigning the main questionnaire form with decorative elements and an
  enhanced progress indicator, and overhauling the intro section with a hero and
  feature cards. All core UI components (checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders,
  progress bar, cards) were updated for a more polished and consistent look. A
  key decision was to apply these new styling principles consistently across all
  14 questionnaire sections and the final report section, replacing old generic
  gray boxes with new themed card-style groupings.

  During the process, a console error related to  values being passed to
  input fields was identified and fixed by modifying the  component to
  safely handle  values. The outcome is a visually cohesive, professional,
  and aesthetically pleasing sleep questionnaire app that aligns with the user's
  goal of a "beautiful" design.
